    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter">
                <head type="title">Miklós Oláh to Kristóf Batthyány (Graz, 14 January 1553)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p>Oláh has understood what Kristóf Batthyány wrote in his letter. He is
                            also sorry to hear that Batthyány is facing so many difficulties, and
                            that the feud between him and his uncle, Ferenc Batthyány is not over,
                            either. Oláh would be glad to mediate between them, and if he can
                            achieve something, he will let him know through the man in Varaždin
                            because he has sent Batthyány’s man back to him so he does not have to
                            bear that cost. He thanks Batthyány for the game meat he sent.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p>Magnifice Domine et Amice nobis Honorandissime, salutem et nostri
                    commendationem! </p>
                <p>Ea, quae nobis Magnificentia Vestra in litteris suis significavit,
                    clare intelleximus. Dolemus sane Dominationem Vestram in tantis molestiis
                    constitutam esse et differentiis controversiisque, quae inter Magnificentiam
                    Vestram et magnificum dominum <persName>Franciscum de Batthyan</persName><note
                        type="critic">Ferenc Batthyány.</note> patruum eiusdem vertuntur, nullum
                    unquam finem imponi. Nos libenter Dominationis Vestrae causa apud ipsum dominum
                        <persName>Franciscum</persName>
                    <choice>
                        <orig>parteis</orig>
                        <supplied>partes</supplied>
                    </choice> nostras interponemus laborabimusque, si quid boni efficere poterimus,
                    et quicquid perfecerimus aut egerimus, Dominationi Vestrae per hominem
                        Varasdiensem<note type="critic">We do not know him more closely.</note>
                    significabimus. Hominem autem Dominationis Vestrae hic retinere noluimus, ne
                    faceret sumptus, sed ad Dominationem Vestram remisimus. Pro ferinis carnibus ac
                    aliis, quae nobis Dominatio Vestra Magnifica misit, eidem agimus gratias, et
                    quod nostri memor fuit, nos vicissim mutua amicitia Dominationi Vestrae non
                    deerimus, eandem feliciter valere optamus. </p>
                <p><placeName>Graczy</placeName> 14. Ianuarii anno Domini 1553.</p>
                <p>
                    <seg type="signature">
                        <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">Vester Agriensis etc. manu
                            propria.</add>
                    </seg>
                </p>
                <pb/>
            </div>
            <div style="handwritten" type="verso">
                <head>On the outer side:</head>
                <p>Magnifico domino Christophoro de Batthyan pincernarum regalium
                    magistro etc. domino et amico nobis honorandissimo.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
